{
  "answer": "**The *Pārāśara Smṛti* (work slug: `unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be`), Chapter 7 (\"The Purification of Things\"), contains the relevant passage.**[^1]\n\nThe verses assign the names as follows:\n\n> An eight-year-old girl is a Gaurī; a nine-year-old is a Rohiṇī.[^2]  \n> A ten-year-old girl is a Kanyā; after that, she is a *rajasvalā* (a menstruating woman).[^3]\n\nThe subsequent sanction regarding the twelfth year states:\n\n> He who does not give his daughter in marriage when she has reached her twelfth year, her ancestors themselves drink her menstrual blood month after month.[^4]\n\nThese are verses *Par_7.4–7.6*.\n\n[^1]: *Pārāśara Smṛti*, Chapter 7, [translation](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/07/translation/).\n[^2]: *Pārāśara Smṛti*, Chapter 7 (*Par_7.4*), [paragraph](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/07/translation/#p-dda364/).\n[^3]: *Pārāśara Smṛti*, Chapter 7 (*Par_7.5*, first sentence), [paragraph](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/07/translation/#p-4665dc/).\n[^4]: *Pārāśara Smṛti*, Chapter 7 (*Par_7.5–7.6*), [passage](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/07/translation/#p-4665dc/#p-513c49/).",
